\title{Set of all functions}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[paul-r-halmos]] [[halmos-1974-naive]] Ch.8}
\MML{funct_2}{def 2}{K1}

\p{Let #{X} and #{Y} be sets. We denote the \define{Set of all functions} from #{X} to #{Y} as either #{Y^{X}} or #{\hom(X,Y)}.}

\p{We see this really is a set, since a function is a subset of #{X\times Y}, so the set of all functions is a subset of #{\powerset{X\times Y}}.}